     <body>
     <div type="poem">
   <head>Uerses in praise of the Booke.</head>
   <lg>
      <l>WHere Vertue takes his habitation,</l>
      <l>There all the Graces like <hi>Pedisequae,</hi>
      </l>
      <l>Doe burnish and adorne the roome: The mind</l>
      <l>Then being simply pure, is capable</l>
      <l>Of eu'ry noble forme, and sendeth forth</l>
      <l>The Christall streames of pleasing Eloquence<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1+ letters">
            <desc>•…</desc>
         </gap>
      </l>
      <l>Peruse this Worke: Here hath Dame <hi>Arete</hi>
      </l>
      <l>Inclos'd herselfe, and Art as swift, as is</l>
      <l>The speedy <hi>Hind,</hi> doth striue to beautifie</l>
      <l>Each Line and Leafe with Learnings attributes.</l>
      <l>Reade then: and Errours which are obuious</l>
      <l>"Interpret mildely. <hi>The great'st enemy</hi>
      </l>
      <l>"<hi>That Science hath, is obtuse Ignorance.</hi>
      </l>
   </lg>
   <p>
      <hi>Alexander Burlacy</hi> Esquire.</p>
</div>
